tag.desc: `{p1}` must not have other alias
pointer `{p}` must be properly aligned for type `{T}`
the reference of `{p}` must outlive the lifetime `{l}`
the memory range `[{p}, {p} + sizeof({T})*{len})` must be allocated by allocator `{A}`
pointer `{p}` must be dereferencable in the `sizeof({T})*{len}` memory from it
tag.expr: Allocated(p, T, len, *) && InBound(p, T, len)

tag.desc: the pointer `{p}` and its offset up to `sizeof({T})*{len}` must point to a single allocated object
tag.expr: mem(p, p+ sizeof(T) * len)  single allocated object

tag.desc: the memory range `[{p}, {p} + sizeof({T})*{len}]` must be fully initialized for type `{T}`
tag.expr: i  0..len, mem(p + sizeof(T) * i, p + sizeof(T) * (i+1)) = valid(T)

tag.desc: the memory pointed by `{p}` must remain consistent with `{layout}`
tag.expr: ValidNum(rem(p, layout.align), 0) && Allocated(p, u8, layout.size, heap)

tag.desc: type `{T}` must have no padding bytes
pointer `{p}` must not be null
the memory ranges `[{dst}, {dst} + sizeof({T})*{len})` and `[{src}, {src} + sizeof({T})*{len}]` must not overlap
the pointer `{p}` doesn't hold exclusive ownership of its reference
the memory access of `[{p}, {p} + sizeof({T})*{len}]` must be volatile
!Size
the file descriptor `{fd}` must be valid and open
the pointer `{p}` must hold exclusive ownership of its reference
pointer `{p}` must remain at the same memory address for the duration of lifetime `{l}`
the reference conversion of the pointer `{p}` must be valid
the size of type `{T}` should be `{c}`
if type `{T}` implements trait `{trait}`, the property `{property}` is mitigated
the pointer `{p}` must point to a value of `{T}`
the current program point should not be reachable during execution
the value `{x}` must be `Some({T})`
the memory range `[{p}, {p} + {len} + 1]` must contain a valid C-style string
the value of `{exp}` must lie within the valid `{vrange}`
pointer `{p}` must be valid for reading and writing the `sizeof({T})*{len}` memory from it
the memory range `{arange}` must contain valid UTF-8 bytes
